{"entity":{"id":"recGmIF4O1jGzaWSs","type":"chapter","slug":"recGmIF4O1jGzaWSs","label":"Job.18","rawId":"recGmIF4O1jGzaWSs","book":{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","slug":"job","label":"Job","subtitle":"Poetry-Wisdom","count":1070,"description":"42 chapters, 190 people, 6 places"}},"stats":{"verses":21,"people":2,"places":0,"events":1},"nodes":[{"id":"recGmIF4O1jGzaWSs","type":"chapter","group":"focus","label":"Job.18","slug":"job_18","score":21},{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","group":"book","label":"Job","slug":"job","score":1070},{"id":"rectCt5FFUjDdSPnY","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Bildad","slug":"bildad_499","score":1},{"id":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"God","slug":"god_1324","score":1},{"id":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","type":"event","group":"event","label":"Job's Trial","slug":"event-117","score":21}],"links":[{"source":"recGmIF4O1jGzaWSs","target":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","label":"part of"},{"source":"recGmIF4O1jGzaWSs","target":"rectCt5FFUjDdSPnY","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recGmIF4O1jGzaWSs","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recGmIF4O1jGzaWSs","target":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"rectU3CDArB8BqoZo","ref":"Job.18.1","text":"Then answered Bildad the Shuhite, and said,","year":-1520},{"id":"recwR62pf6nQiNqKM","ref":"Job.18.2","text":"How long will it be ere ye make an end of words? mark, and afterwards we will speak.","year":-1520},{"id":"recEB90Gf4Kd5vAO7","ref":"Job.18.3","text":"Wherefore are we counted as beasts, and reputed vile in your sight?","year":-1520},{"id":"recgpjxm7ZpeBaf23","ref":"Job.18.4","text":"He teareth himself in his anger: shall the earth be forsaken for thee? and shall the rock be removed out of his place?","year":-1520},{"id":"recLoXTDiNoyosiCq","ref":"Job.18.5","text":"Yea, the light of the wicked shall be put out, and the spark of his fire shall not shine.","year":-1520},{"id":"rec4LwMyIhwrxfZKu","ref":"Job.18.6","text":"The light shall be dark in his tabernacle, and his candle shall be put out with him.","year":-1520},{"id":"recr4SsthmRaB1Dmz","ref":"Job.18.7","text":"The steps of his strength shall be straitened, and his own counsel shall cast him down.","year":-1520},{"id":"recXHTpi5HemDXClQ","ref":"Job.18.8","text":"For he is cast into a net by his own feet, and he walketh upon a snare.","year":-1520}]}
